    "updated_at": "2014-10-19T00:13:44Z",
    "body": "A proc has the same behavior, so this isn't a difference with unboxed closures in particular.  It strikes me as intentional since rust defaults to immutability, and the only place where you can specify that you want mutability is on the original binding.  You can always write something like this instead:\n\n``` rust\nlet x = 0u;\n...\nlet mut x_copy = x;\nlet f = move |&mut:| x_copy = 42;\n```\n",
