    "updated_at": "2015-01-24T22:45:08Z",
    "body": "The closure in the original example is capturing by reference, not by value as the description implies. In any case I added a test covering all the tests and will close this issue -- everything seems to be behaving reasonably. The one thing that surprised me is that you can mutate a variable declared as `let` from within a `FnMut` closure; it makes sense when you consider the desugaring. This seems to be the case that @japaric was initially attempting to test, and it indeed works as he predicted. I am not sure yet if this is a bug though.\n",
